{"id":"thousands","term":"Thousands","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Micah 5:2\">Micah 5:2</a>), another name for “families” or “clans” (see <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 1:16\">Num. 1:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 10:4\">10:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 22:14\">Josh. 22:14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 22:21\">21</a>). Several “thousands” or “families” made up a “tribe.”</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Micah 5:2","Numbers 1:16","Numbers 10:4","Joshua 22:14","Joshua 22:21"]}